(9,1,'page','published','2010-10-15 13:53:17','2011-05-19 02:43:53',50,'in_the_news','In The News','<p>	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><p>	Welcome to our news page. Check here for frequent updates on press coverage and media appearances featuring Ventus Medical and Provent Therapy. We invite you to read these articles about Provent Therapy:</p><ul>	<li>		<p>			<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/biz0051-01.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span dir=\"ltr\" title=\"\">PRESENTATION AT AMERICAN THORACIC SOCIETY<br />			ANNUAL MEETING FURTHER DEMONSTRATES MECHANISM<br />			OF ACTION FOR PROVENT&reg; SLEEP APNEA THERAPY </span></a></p>	</li>	<li>		<p>			<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HmfufUmxBbc\" target=\"_blank\"><span dir=\"ltr\" title=\"Provent: New Therapy for Sleep Apnea\">Provent</span><span dir=\"ltr\" title=\"Provent: New Therapy for Sleep Apnea\">: New Therapy for Sleep Apnea</span></a></p>	</li>	<li>		<p>			<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/uploads/mdd.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Ventus</span> gets &quot;bulletproof&quot; data that <span>PROVENT</span> works</a></p>	</li>	<li>		<p>			<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0207-01_a_sleep_apnea_devices_website.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Sleep Apnea Devices: The Changing Of The Guard</a></p>	</li></ul><p>	&nbsp;</p><p>	&nbsp;</p><p>	&nbsp;</p><p>	&nbsp;</p><p>	&nbsp;</p><p>	&nbsp;</p>',11,0,'blog.template.php'),
(11,1,'page','published','2010-10-15 22:20:25','2011-03-24 20:32:42',2,'about_provent','About Provent','<h1>	A new, breakthrough treatment for obstructive sleep apnea</h1><h3>	About Provent Therapy</h3><p>	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><p>	Have you decided CPAP isn&rsquo;t for you? Finally, there is an alternative&mdash;a new treatment clinically proven to treat obstructive sleep apnea (OSA) and related snoring&mdash;that does not require struggling with a CPAP machine.</p><p>	Provent Therapy uses a proprietary MicroValve design that creates pressure when you exhale to keep your airway open. The devices attach over the nostrils with a hypoallergenic adhesive. It&rsquo;s small and disposable, making it discreet and very convenient. If you&rsquo;re looking for an alternative to CPAP, Provent Therapy could be your ideal obstructive sleep apnea solution.</p><h3>	Why Provent Therapy</h3><p>	Many former CPAP users are now enjoying brighter days and better sleep with their sleep partners &mdash; all thanks to this innovative, award-winning, FDA-cleared device for the treatment of OSA. <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/why_provent_therapy\"><strong>Read more!</strong></a></p><h3>	How to use</h3><p>	Most patients find Provent Therapy very easy to use, especially in comparison to a CPAP machine. It requires no mask, tubes, or machine; just a set of two small devices worn over the nostrils. <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/how_to_use\"><strong>Read more!</strong></a></p><h3>	Benefits</h3><p>	Provent Therapy is a new treatment for obstructive sleep apnea. Studies have shown that treating OSA can reduce health risks (like depression and heart disease) associated with the disease. Provent Therapy has been proven to<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>1</sup></span>:</p><ul>	<li>		Decrease apneas (breathing pauses)</li>	<li>		Increase your energy</li>	<li>		Reduce daytime sleepiness</li>	<li>		Lead to a better quality of sleep</li>	<li>		Reduce OSA-related snoring</li>	<li>		Increase your enthusiasm to get things done</li>	<li>		Improve your sleep</li></ul><p>	<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/benefits\"><strong>Read more about benefits associated with treating obstructive sleep apnea.</strong></a></p><h3>	FAQs</h3><p>	Want to know more about Provent Therapy and where you can get it? <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/faq\"><strong>Read the Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs).</strong></a></p><p>	&nbsp;</p><hr /><p>	<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>1</sup>Data on file</span></p>',0,0,'provent_mainpage.template.php'),
(12,1,'page','published','2010-10-15 22:34:27','2011-03-01 05:03:59',0,'why_provent_therapy','Why Provent Therapy','<h1>	Why Provent Therapy</h1><h3>	A convenient and effective alternative that fits your lifestyle</h3><p>	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><p>	Provent Therapy is discreet, disposable, and simple to operate. It requires no masks, tubes, or machines. It&rsquo;s also small and convenient, so it&rsquo;s easy to take with you if you&rsquo;re away overnight.</p><p>	Provent Therapy may take some getting used to but most patients agree it&rsquo;s worth it. In as little as three nights, you could be sleeping more quietly and peacefully. And Provent patients have been shown to wake up refreshed and are better able to focus on daily tasks.</p><p>	You&rsquo;re also likely to enjoy better sleep with your sleep partner, especially if he or she is bothered by your snoring or CPAP machine. Of course, like anything new, it requires patience. You might not see results right away, and it can take a few nights before it becomes a comfortable part of your sleep routine.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/benefits\">Learn more about the benefits of this CPAP alternative.</a></p><h3>	A great solution for sleep partners</h3><p>	Obstructive sleep apnea isn&rsquo;t just tough on patients, it&rsquo;s tough on relationships. The Provent Nasal Device can help people with OSA overcome many of the problems associated with OSA. And your partner will rest assured that you are being treated.</p><p>	Clinical studies have shown that 83% of subjects experienced a snoring reduction with Provent Therapy<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>1</sup></span>.&nbsp; And among OSA subjects that snored, Provent Therapy reduced snoring to trace or none in 58%<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>2</sup></span>. It can also improve daytime alertness and mental function. Plus, it&rsquo;s discreet, and noise free, allowing you and your sleep partner to sleep in the same room without a machine. Best of all, you can be assured that while you are handling your obstructive sleep apnea, you are also helping your partner get a peaceful night&rsquo;s sleep.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/sleep_partners\">Find more information for sleep partners.</a></p><h3>	See how Provent works</h3><p>	<video height=\"280\" id=\"clinvid\" poster=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/video/how_it_works.jpg\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/video/how_it_works.m4v\" tabindex=\"0\" width=\"372\"></video><script>jwplayer(\"clinvid\").setup({    flashplayer: \"http://www.proventtherapy.com/jwplayer/player.swf\"  });</script></p><p>	OSA leads to narrowing of the airway, which can cause disrupted sleep. Over time, chronic sleep disruptions can make you feel tired, and lead to many health problems.</p><p>	The Provent Nasal Device fits over both nostrils and uses a proprietary MicroValve design that creates pressure which keeps the airway open. As you inhale, airflow is nearly unobstructed, allowing for normal breathing. As you exhale, the MicroValve closes, directing air through small air channels, increasing resistance. This resistance creates EPAP (Expiratory Positive Airway Pressure), which props open the airway until you inhale again.</p><p>	Provent works much like CPAP therapy, except instead of an external machine, your own breathing creates the pressure that keeps your airway open. Like CPAP, it needs to be worn every night to effectively relieve symptoms of OSA. It may take time before you start to feel like you&rsquo;re sleeping normally and waking up refreshed.</p><p>	For many patients, the Provent Device is an effective treatment for OSA while allowing them more freedom to travel, enjoy their sleep partner, and live their lives.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/how_to_use\">Get more details on how to use this CPAP alternative.</a></p><p>	In a recent market research study, Provent users were asked to rate Provent Therapy and indicate what they liked about it<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>3</sup></span>:</p><ul>	<li>		No machine or mask involved (84%)</li>	<li>		Convenient for travel (80%)</li>	<li>		It&rsquo;s discreet; I am comfortable wearing it with my sleep partner (51%)</li>	<li>		My snoring has improved (50%)</li></ul><p>	We also heard the following comments from satisfied Provent Therapy patients<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>4</sup></span>:</p><blockquote>	&ldquo;CPAP compared to Provent, there&rsquo;s no comparison. Provent &ndash; it&rsquo;s a miracle; so little, so easy. Traveling: it&rsquo;s very little to take along. It&rsquo;s really easy to put in. Other than some initial getting used to &ndash; it&rsquo;s like nothing&rsquo;s there!&rdquo;</blockquote><p style=\"text-align: right\">	<em>-Marsha</em></p><blockquote>	&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve had tonsils, adenoids, soft palate, and sinus surgeries which only lasted a few months in treating my sleep apnea. I&rsquo;ve used an oral appliance which worked for a few years. I could never sleep with a CPAP machine but I&rsquo;m sticking with Provent&hellip;it&rsquo;s easy, disposable,and it works!&rdquo;</blockquote><p style=\"text-align: right\">	<em>-Bill</em></p><p>	<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/success_stories\">Read about Maria and Angela, two people with obstructive sleep apnea who used PROVENT Therapy to have better nights, and more alert days.</a></p><p>	&nbsp;</p><hr /><address>	<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>1</sup><em> Colrain IM, Brooks S, Black J. A pilot evaluation of a nasal expiratory resistance device for the treatment of obstructive sleep apnea. Journal of Clinical Sleep Medicine2008;4(5):426-433</em></span></address><address>	<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>2</sup> Data on file</span></address><address>	<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>3</sup> Kern Mueller Group, Provent Patient Research February 2010&nbsp;</span></address><address>	<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>4</sup> Patient data on file</span></address>',11,0,'how_to_use.template.php'),
(13,1,'page','published','2010-10-15 22:35:29','2011-03-29 11:45:36',0,'how_to_use','How To Use','<h1>	Getting started with Provent Therapy</h1><p>	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><p>	The Provent device, a clinically-proven treatment for OSA, is designed to be a hassle-free alternative to CPAP therapy. It&rsquo;s simple to incorporate into your nightly routine, and will help you enjoy more restful sleep and brighter, more energized days.</p><h3>	Applying the Provent Devices</h3><div class=\"step\">	<img src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/gfx_htu_step1.png\" />	<h4>		STEP 1</h4>	<p>		Peel the adhesive from the paper backing.</p></div><div class=\"step\">	<img src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/gfx_htu_step2.png\" />	<h4>		STEP 2</h4>	<p>		Align the long end of the nasal insert with the long end of your nostrils. Make sure the side tab points outward.</p></div><div class=\"step\">	<img src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/gfx_htu_step3.png\" />	<h4>		STEP 3</h4>	<p>		Once aligned, place a nasal insert into the nostril. Stretch the lower nostril by pulling down on the skin below it, as if shaving the area above the upper lip. This will help ensure a good seal.</p>	<p>		If a device is not positioned correctly, remove it and try repositioning it. Keep in mind, though, that repeated repositioning will weaken the adhesive, which can reduce the ability to get a complete seal and reduce the device&rsquo;s effectiveness.</p></div><div class=\"step\">	<img src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/gfx_htu_step4.png\" />	<h4>		STEP 4</h4>	<p>		Gently press down around the adhesive to ensure a good seal. Make sure there are no folds or creases, which can compromise the seal.</p></div><div class=\"step\">	<img src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/gfx_htu_step5.png\" />	<h4>		STEP 5</h4>	<p>		Once in place, the adhesive tab should be adhered as shown. Repeat this process for the other nostril. Use a mirror to check that both devices are properly fitted. To remove the Provent Nasal Device, gently peel the adhesive away from the nostril. Throw the used devices away, as they are for one-time use only.</p>	<p>		<video height=\"280\" id=\"howvid\" poster=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/video/full_acclimation.jpg\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/video/full_acclimation.m4v\" tabindex=\"0\" width=\"372\"></video><script>jwplayer(\"howvid\").setup({    flashplayer: \"http://www.proventtherapy.com/jwplayer/player.swf\"  });</script></p>	<h3>		Provent Application and Use Guide</h3>	<p>		For more details about applying and wearing the Provent Nasal Device, <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/uploads/lbl0227-01_a_one-page_acclimation_guide_for_dmes.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">download this helpful application and usage guide</a>.</p>	<h3>		How to get a prescription</h3>	<p>		<span x=\"y\">Provent Therapy is available by prescription only, so you need to ask your doctor if it&rsquo;s right for you. The easiest way to begin is to request a </span><a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/10_night_trial\"><span x=\"y\">10-night trial</span></a><span x=\"y\">. If you want more information to take to your doctor, download and print these two documents:</span></p>	<ul>		<li>			<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0174-01_take_to_your_doctor.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span x=\"y\">Information Guide</span></a></li>		<li>			<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0217-01_a_generic_do_form.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span x=\"y\">Doctor Order Form</span></a></li>		<li>			<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/supplier_locator\">List of Suppliers</a></li>	</ul></div>',11,0,'how_to_use.template.php'),
(14,1,'page','published','2010-10-15 22:36:27','2011-03-29 11:48:15',0,'benefits','Benefits','<h1>	Benefits of treating OSA</h1><h3>	A new obstructive sleep apnea solution with proven health benefits</h3><p>	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><p>	<img src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/gfx_bene_eating.png\" style=\"padding-right: 10px; float: left\" /> The Provent Nasal Device is a clinically effective, prescription-only device for the treatment of obstructive sleep apnea (OSA). Unlike a CPAP machine, the Provent Device does not require cumbersome equipment or even electricity. Instead it employs a proprietary MicroValve design to create Expiratory Positive Airway Pressure (EPAP) to keep the airway open during sleep.</p><p>	With the airway no longer obstructed, users can enjoy better, more restful sleep &mdash; and more energized, productive days. According to the National Heart, Lung, and Blood Institute, untreated OSA can lead to:</p><ol>	<li>		Excessive daytime sleepiness</li>	<li>		High blood pressure</li>	<li>		Obesity</li>	<li>		Greater risk of heart attack, heart failure, and stroke</li>	<li>		Greater risk of diabetes</li>	<li>		Increased chance of driving accidents and work-related injuries</li></ol><p>	As an alternative to CPAP, Provent Therapy has been shown to provide the following benefits:</p><ol>	<li>		Improved daytime function</li>	<li>		Improved enthusiasm to get things done</li>	<li>		Reduced breathing disruptions during sleep</li>	<li>		Reduced snoring</li>	<li>		Increased blood oxygenation levels</li></ol><h3>	Differences between CPAP and Provent</h3><p>	CPAP uses continuous positive airway pressure to keep the airway from collapsing. Provent Therapy uses the power of your own breathing, expiratory positive airway pressure, to create this pressure, as opposed to forced air from an air blower.</p><p>	Some CPAP users give up treatment (or use it less than they should) because they find the equipment cumbersome and difficult to use.</p><p>	In comparison with CPAP, the Provent Device offers multiple benefits that enhance ease of use and comfort. For many former CPAP users, Provent Therapy is an alternative to CPAP that fits their lifestyle while giving them the freedom they&rsquo;ve been missing.</p><h3>	Get started today!</h3><p>	<span x=\"y\">Provent Therapy is available by prescription only, so you need to ask your doctor if it&rsquo;s right for you. The easiest way to begin is to request a&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/10_night_trial\"><span x=\"y\">10-night trial</span></a><span x=\"y\">. If you want more information to take to your doctor, download and print these two documents:</span></p><ul>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0174-01_take_to_your_doctor.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span x=\"y\">Information Guide</span></a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0217-01_a_generic_do_form.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span x=\"y\">Doctor Order Form</span></a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/supplier_locator\">List of Suppliers</a></li></ul>',11,0,'benefits.template.php'),
(15,1,'page','published','2010-10-16 18:57:33','2011-04-08 05:03:05',0,'faq','FAQ','<h2>	Frequently Asked Questions</h2><p>	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><ol>	<li>		<a href=\"#a1\">What is Provent Therapy?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a2\">What is EPAP?</a><a name=\"a24\"></a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a3\">How does Provent Therapy work?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a4\">Is Provent Therapy FDA-cleared?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a5\">Is Provent Therapy right for me?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a6\">Does Provent Therapy stop snoring?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a7\">Why is it important to treat obstructive sleep apnea?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a8\">How is Provent Therapy different from CPAP therapy?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a9\">Can Provent Therapy replace my CPAP machine?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a10\">Can I travel with Provent Therapy?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a11\">Can I use this device with my CPAP?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a12\">Who makes Provent Therapy?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a13\">Do I need a prescription for Provent Therapy?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a14\">How do I talk to my doctor about Provent Therapy?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a15\">How can I request a 10-night trial of Provent Therapy?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a16\">What is the cost for the 10-night trial?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a17\">Can Provent Therapy be used in children?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a18\">Where can I get a list of suppliers that carry Provent Therapy?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a19\">What can I expect from my initial experience with Provent Therapy?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a20\">Will Provent work for me?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a21\">Is Provent Therapy safe?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a22\">Is Provent Therapy covered by my insurance?</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"#a23\">Is Provent Therapy available outside of the United States?</a><br />		&nbsp;</li></ol><h3>	1. What is Provent Therapy?<a name=\"a1\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	PROVENT Sleep Apnea Therapy is a simple, non-invasive treatment for obstructive sleep apnea (OSA). The Provent Nasal Device uses a valve design that attaches over the nostrils and is secured in place with hypoallergenic adhesive. The valve opens and closes, redirecting air through small holes to create resistance upon breathing out. Because it&#39;s a small, single use, disposable device, it&#39;s also discreet and very convenient.</p><h3>	2. What is EPAP?<a name=\"a2\"></a></h3><p>	Provent Sleep Apnea Therapy utilizes a proprietary MicroValve technology developed by Ventus Medical. The device attaches over the nostrils with a hypoallergenic adhesive. During inhalation, the valve opens, allowing the user to breathe in freely. When exhaling, the valve closes and air passing through the nose is directed through two small air channels. This increases the pressure in the airway (called EPAP or expiratory positive airway pressure). This maintains pressure in the airway until the start of the next inspiration and helps to keep it open.</p><h3>	3. How does Provent Therapy work?<a name=\"a3\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	PROVENT Therapy utilizes a proprietary MicroValve technology developed by Ventus Medical. The device attaches over the nostrils. During inhalation, the valve opens, allowing the user to breathe in freely. When exhaling, the valve closes and air passing through the nose is directed through two small air channels. This increases the pressure in the airway and helps to keep it open.</p><h3>	4. Is Provent Therapy FDA-cleared?<a name=\"a4\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	Provent therapy was cleared by the US FDA for the treatment of OSA.</p><h3>	5. Is Provent Therapy right for me?<a name=\"a5\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	Provent Therapy may not be appropriate for everyone. If you have been diagnosed with OSA and you are considering Provent Therapy, you should speak to your physician to evaluate your individual medical needs.<span _fck_bookmark=\"1\" style=\"display: none\">&nbsp;</span></p><h3>	6. Does Provent Therapy stop snoring?<a name=\"a6\"></a></h3><p>	Clinical studies have shown that 83% of patients experienced a snoring reduction with Provent Therapy<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>1</sup></span>. Among OSA patients that snore, Provent Therapy virtually eliminated snoring in 58% of patients<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>2</sup></span>.</p><h3>	7. Why is it important to treat obstructive sleep apnea?<a name=\"a7\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	There is no cure for obstructive sleep apnea. Untreated OSA has a number of potential serious side effects. These include excessive daytime sleepiness, increased risk of high blood pressure, heart attack, stroke, diabetes, depression, increased risk or worsening of heart failure, and increased likelihood of driving or work-related accidents.</p><h3>	8. How is Provent Therapy different from CPAP therapy?<a name=\"a8\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	CPAP increases the pressure on both inspiration and expiration, while Provent Therapy increases the pressure on expiration only. CPAP increases pressure in the airway using forced air, while Provent Therapy uses the patient&rsquo;s own breathing to create pressure during exhalation.</p><h3>	9. Can Provent Therapy replace my CPAP machine?<a name=\"a9\"></a></h3><p>	If you are not using your CPAP machine all night, every night then you might ask your physician about non-CPAP alternatives including Provent Therapy. Only you and your physician can decide what therapy is best for you.&nbsp;If you want more information to take to your doctor, download and print this <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0174-01_take_to_your_doctor.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">information guide</a> and&nbsp;<span _fck_bookmark=\"1\" style=\"display: none\">&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0217-01_a_generic_do_form.pdf\">doctor order form</a>.&nbsp;</p><h3>	10. Can I travel with Provent Therapy?<a name=\"a10\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	Because of its small, simple design, traveling is easy with Provent Therapy. There is no need for electricity or equipment, and the device is single-use. Just use a new set every night.</p><h3>	11. Can I use this device with my CPAP?<a name=\"a11\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	Provent Therapy cannot be used together with a CPAP machine, but some users find that it&rsquo;s more convenient to use PROVENT when traveling and CPAP when at home.</p><h3>	12. Who makes Provent Therapy?<a name=\"a12\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	Ventus Medical is the maker of Provent&reg; Sleep Apnea Therapy and is focused on positively changing the lives of people with sleep-disordered breathing.</p><h3>	13. Do I need a prescription for Provent Therapy?<a name=\"a13\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	Yes, Provent Therapy is a prescription-only product. Ask your physician if it&rsquo;s right for you.</p><h3>	14. How do I talk to my doctor about Provent Therapy?<a name=\"a14\"></a></h3><p>	If you are interested in speaking to your doctor about Provent Therapy, <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0174-01_take_to_your_doctor.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">click here to download a document to bring to your doctor</a>.</p><h3>	15. How can I request a 10-night trial of Provent Therapy?<a name=\"a15\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	If you are interested in obtaining a prescription for the 10-night trial, simply ask your doctor or&nbsp;<a href=\"http://96.31.169.199/10_night_trial\">click here to request additional information</a>.</p><h3>	16. What is the cost for the 10-night trial?<a name=\"a16\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	There is a nominal cost associated with the 10-night trial that is set by the supplier. Suggested retail price is less than $20.<span _fck_bookmark=\"1\" style=\"display: none\">&nbsp;</span></p><h3>	17. Can Provent Therapy be used in children?<a name=\"a17\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	No, the safety and effectiveness of Provent Therapy in children under the age of 18 has not been established.</p><h3>	18. Where can I get a list of suppliers that carry Provent Therapy?<a name=\"a18\"></a></h3><p>	For a list of names and contact information for Provent Therapy suppliers, <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/supplier_locator\">click here</a> . Please note that these are national distributors and can ship to any location in the US.</p><h3>	19. What can I expect from my initial experience with Provent Therapy?<a name=\"a19\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	After you apply the Provent Device, you should notice the resistance created as you try to exhale. Generally, users get used to this feeling after wearing for several nights. For tips on how to breathe and how you will feel, <a href=\"/what_to_expect\">click here</a>.</p><h3>	20. Will Provent work for me?<a name=\"a20\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	Provent Therapy does not work for everyone. In recent clinical studies, 72% of obstructive sleep apnea sufferers were successfully treated by PROVENT Therapy. Contact your physician to see if Provent is right for you.</p><h3>	21. Is Provent Therapy safe?<a name=\"a21\"></a></h3><p>	Yes, Provent Therapy can be used safely. In recent clinical studies, no severe, device-related adverse events were reported.&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/lbl0181-01_proventpatientphysicianifu.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Click here for a complete list of warnings, precautions and contraindications</a>.</p><h3>	22. Is Provent Therapy covered by my insurance?<a name=\"a22\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	As Provent Therapy is relatively new, it may not be covered by insurance plans or prescription programs. In many cases, tax-free, flexible spending accounts may be used to cover the cost of Provent Therapy.</p><h3>	23. Is Provent Therapy available outside of the United States?<a name=\"a23\"></a></h3><p class=\"indent\">	At this time, Provent Therapy is only available in the United States. If you wish to be kept informed of future expansion, please <a href=\"#a24\">subscribe to the free e-newsletter above.</a></p><p>	&nbsp;</p><hr /><address>	<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>1</sup>Colrain IM, Brooks S, Black J. A pilot evaluation of a nasal expiratory resistance device for the treatment of obstructive sleep apnea. <em>Journal of Clinical Sleep Medicine</em> 2008;4(5):426-433</span></address><address>	<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>2</sup>Data on file</span></address>',11,0,'faq.template.php'),
(16,1,'page','published','2010-10-16 19:47:37','2011-03-01 05:09:27',3,'obstructive_sleep_apnea','Obstructive Sleep Apnea','<h1>	Learn more about Obstructive Sleep Apnea</h1><h3>	What is Obstructive Sleep Apnea<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>1</sup></span>?</h3><p>	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><p>	A common disorder, Obstructive Sleep Apnea (OSA) is characterized by pauses in breathing or shallow breaths during sleep. OSA is a chronic condition, which means it does not resolve spontaneously, and is rarely cured.</p><p>	When people with OSA fall asleep, they can stop breathing for a few seconds to a minute. These interruptions happen throughout the night, at least five times an hour. Afterward, normal breathing starts again, sometimes with a loud snort or choking sound.</p><p>	When breathing pauses or becomes shallow, the OSA sufferer usually moves out of deep sleep into light sleep&mdash;or has a brief awakening&mdash;which they may not remember. As a result of these disruptions, sleep quality is worsened, causing tiredness during the day. In fact, obstructive sleep apnea is one of the leading causes of daytime sleepiness.</p><h3>	Symptoms and Signs of Obstructive Sleep Apnea<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>2</sup></span></h3><p>	Loud frequent snoring, increased age and obesity with increased neck size are the three best predictors of having OSA. If your partner complains about your snoring or says that you gasp for breath during the night (especially if you make a loud snorting or choking sound), this is a sign you might have obstructive sleep apnea. Other symptoms may include one or more of the following:</p><ul>	<li>		Sleepiness during the day</li>	<li>		Morning headaches</li>	<li>		Memory, learning, or concentration problems</li>	<li>		Irritability, depression, mood swings, or personality changes</li>	<li>		Needing to urinate at night</li>	<li>		Waking up with a dry throat</li></ul><p>	Of course, not all people who show these symptoms have obstructive sleep apnea. If you experience these symptoms, tell your doctor, who will review your history, and possibly perform non-invasive tests to make a diagnosis. Obstructive sleep apnea ranges in severity, and can be mild, moderate, or severe. And while there is no cure for obstructive sleep apnea, there is treatment that can help reduce snoring, and help you get better sleep.</p><h3>	What Causes Obstructive Sleep Apnea<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>2</sup></span>?</h3><p>	People with OSA tend to have a narrower or more collapsible airway than normal, often at the base of the tongue and soft palate. During sleep, the normal relaxation of muscles in the throat can cause the tongue and palate to fall backwards, further closing the already narrowed airway. Obstructive sleep apnea can be caused (or made worse) by:</p><ul>	<li>		Obesity: Extra fat tissue in the neck can narrow the airway, which makes it harder to keep open</li>	<li>		Large tongue and tonsils: These can obstruct the airway, making it harder for air to pass through</li>	<li>		Getting older: For reasons not fully understood, sleep apnea tends to increase with age</li>	<li>		Head and neck shape: Some people have a naturally small airway opening in the mouth and throat due the structure of their bones</li></ul><h3>	Health risks of Obstructive Sleep Apnea<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>2</sup></span>.</h3><p>	Left untreated, Obstructive Sleep Apnea can trigger the release of stress hormones, change how your body uses energy, and, of course, make you feel tired and sleepy during the day. But even if you don&rsquo;t have daytime sleepiness, obstructive sleep apnea still puts you at higher risk for:</p><ul>	<li>		High blood pressure</li>	<li>		Heart attack, heart failure</li>	<li>		Stroke</li>	<li>		Irregular heartbeats</li>	<li>		Diabetes</li>	<li>		Obesity</li>	<li>		Driving or work-related accidents</li></ul><h3>	Treatment for Obstructive Sleep Apnea</h3><p>	In addition to lifestyle changes and surgery, CPAP therapy has been an accepted treatment for OSA. A CPAP machine is a blower that connects by a tube to a mask that fits over your mouth or nose, blowing air so that a continuous pressure in the airway is maintained. This constant pressure keeps the airway from collapsing allowing normal breathing.</p><p>	Some people have difficulty using a CPAP machine and others don&rsquo;t like to travel with their CPAP equipment. Fortunately, there&rsquo;s now an alternative to CPAP that requires no mask, no machine, and no electricity.</p><p>	The Provent Nasal Device is small, discreet, and easy to use. Best of all, it&rsquo;s clinically proven to treat obstructive sleep apnea and related snoring by using the power of your own breathing to stabilize your airway. Ask your doctor about using Provent Therapy when you travel, or if a CPAP machine isn&rsquo;t right for you.</p><p>	<strong>If you&rsquo;re interested in this new obstructive sleep apnea treatment, <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//why_provent_therapy\">we&rsquo;ve got all the details right here</a>.&nbsp;So check it out. <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/10_night_trial\">Sign up for a 10-night trial today</a>, and look forward to a better nights&rsquo; sleep.</strong></p><p>	&nbsp;</p><hr /><ul>	<li>		<address>			<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>1</sup>Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (definition of &ldquo;chronic disease&rdquo;)</span></address>		<ul>			<li>				<address>					<span style=\"font-size: 10px\">http://www.cdc.gov/sleep/disorders.htm</span></address>			</li>		</ul>	</li></ul><ul>	<li>		<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>2</sup>National Heart, Lung and Blood Institute (Signs/Symptoms, Diagnosis, Causes, Treatments -&nbsp;i.e. CPAP)</span>		<ul>			<li>				<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-style: italic; font-size: 10px\">http://www.nhlbi.nih.gov/health/dci/Diseases/SleepApnea/SleepApnea_Signs.html</span></li>			<li>				<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-style: italic; font-size: 10px\">http://www.nhlbi.nih.gov/health/dci/Diseases/SleepApnea/SleepApnea_Diagnosis.html</span></li>			<li>				<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-style: italic; font-size: 10px\">http://www.nhlbi.nih.gov/health/dci/Diseases/SleepApnea/SleepApnea_Causes.html</span></li>			<li>				<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-style: italic; font-size: 10px\">http://www.nhlbi.nih.gov/health/dci/Diseases/SleepApnea/</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-style: italic; font-size: 10px\">SleepApnea_Treatments.html</span></li>			<li>				<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-style: italic; font-size: 10px\">http</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-style: italic; font-size: 10px\">://www.nhlbi.nih.gov/health/dci/Diseases/SleepApnea/SleepApnea_Treatments.html</span></li>		</ul>	</li></ul>',0,0,'osa.template.php'),
(17,1,'page','published','2010-10-16 19:48:40','2011-03-29 11:48:58',4,'success_stories','Success Stories','<h1>	Patient Success Stories</h1><h3>	See what real OSA patients have to say</h3><p>	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><p>	More and more people are discovering how effective, easy, and comfortable Provent Therapy can be in treating obstructive sleep apnea. Here, you can meet Angela and Maria, and see what a difference Provent Therapy made in their lives.</p><h4>	MARIA</h4><p>	<strong>Obstructive Sleep Apnea (OSA) Patient</strong></p><p>	<video height=\"280\" id=\"mariavid\" poster=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/video/maria.jpg\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/video/maria.m4v\" tabindex=\"0\" width=\"372\"></video><script>jwplayer(\"mariavid\").setup({    flashplayer: \"http://www.proventtherapy.com/jwplayer/player.swf\"  });</script></p><p>	A retired professor, author, amateur photographer, and certified Braille transcriber, Maria was determined not to let obstructive sleep apnea slow her down. But when diet, exercise, and weight loss weren&rsquo;t enough to treat her symptoms, she reluctantly turned to other options.</p><p>	Initially prescribed CPAP therapy, Maria eventually discontinued it, finding the machine intolerable and cumbersome. Over the course of five years, she also struggled with oral appliances, but daytime sleepiness and other symptoms continued. Frustrated, she asked about newer therapies, and was finally prescribed Provent in July, 2009.</p><p>	Since starting on Provent Therapy, Maria has experienced a nearly complete resolution of her OSA. &ldquo;I&rsquo;m able to sleep through the night, and have a lot more energy during the day,&rdquo; she says. &ldquo;I now use PROVENT every night.&rdquo; With newfound zest for life, she&rsquo;s resumed her active lifestyle, which includes dog sledding, zip-lining, and climbing Machu Picchu in Peru to celebrate her 73rd birthday.</p><h4>	ANGELA</h4><p>	<strong>Obstructive Sleep Apnea (OSA) Patient</strong></p><p>	<video height=\"280\" id=\"angelavid\" poster=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/video/angela.jpg\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/video/angela.m4v\" tabindex=\"0\" width=\"372\"></video><script>jwplayer(\"angelavid\").setup({    flashplayer: \"http://www.proventtherapy.com/jwplayer/player.swf\"  });</script></p><p>	Recently retired from the New York City Department of Education, Angela was looking forward to enjoying her passions, which include dancing, reading, spending time with family, and travel.</p><p>	But obstructive sleep apnea put a damper on her plans. In 2004, she began experiencing symptoms, which included snoring, fatigue, and daytime tiredness. She started treatment using a CPAP machine, but found it extremely challenging to use. The mask left marks on her face each morning, and the cumbersome machine often caused delays at airport security.</p><p>	But then, Angela&rsquo;s doctor gave her samples of Provent Therapy, which led to significant improvement in her OSA symptoms. Angela found PROVENT Therapy to be comfortable and convenient, especially for travel. And she also appreciated the fact that it&rsquo;s disposable, so she no longer had to worry about maintaining and cleaning the device, as she did with CPAP.</p><p>	Today, Angela is more active than ever. &ldquo;With Provent Therapy as my travel companion,&rdquo; she says, &ldquo;I&rsquo;m free to go anywhere.&rdquo;</p><p>	<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold\">Get started today!</span></p><p>	<span x=\"y\">Provent Therapy is available by prescription only, so you need to ask your doctor if it&rsquo;s right for you. The easiest way to begin is to request a&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/10_night_trial\"><span x=\"y\">10-night trial</span></a><span x=\"y\">. If you want more information to take to your doctor, download and print these two documents:</span></p><ul>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0174-01_take_to_your_doctor.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span x=\"y\">Information Guide</span></a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0217-01_a_generic_do_form.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span x=\"y\">Doctor Order Form</span></a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/supplier_locator\">List of Suppliers</a></li></ul>',0,0,'success.template.php'),
(18,1,'page','published','2010-10-16 19:48:56','2011-03-01 07:57:29',5,'sleep_partners','Sleep Partners','<h1>	Better sleep for you and your partner</h1><p>	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><p>	Discover more restful nights&mdash;and more energized days with this CPAP alternative for treating OSA.</p><h3>	Are you worried about your partner&#39;s health?</h3><p>	From loud snoring to gasping for air and abrupt awakening, symptoms of OSA can be unnerving. As hard as it is to see your partner struggling through the night, it&rsquo;s perhaps even more difficult to consider the long-term health risks of untreated OSA, which can include high blood pressure, heart disease, depression and diabetes.</p><p>	Fortunately, OSA can be treated. If your sleep partner suffers from this chronic condition, there are ways you can help him or her get back on the road to better health.</p><h3>	Get the benefit of a good night&rsquo;s sleep.</h3><p>	When your partner experiences sleep disruptions, do you wake up too? Are you bothered by their loud snoring?</p><p>	When your partner is treated with Provent Therapy, it can help you sleep better too. Among OSA patients that snore, Provent Therapy reduced snoring to trace or none in 58%<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>1</sup></span>. Clinical studies have also shown that 83% of patients experienced a snoring reduction with Provent Therapy<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>2</sup></span>. Provent Therapy is clinically proven to improve sleep quality and daytime function and is FDA-cleared for the treatment of OSA.</p><h3>	Don&rsquo;t accept compromises.</h3><p>	Is the equipment your partner uses to treat their OSA causing problems with your bedtime routine? Do you sleep in separate rooms or have to modify when or how you sleep?</p><p>	Provent Therapy is a clinically proven alternative to CPAP. It requires no mask, no machines, and no electricity&mdash;making it easy and convenient to use. In fact, in a clinical trial, four out of five OSA patients who were not compliant with CPAP chose to continue treatment with Provent Therapy past their initial trial.</p><p>	With Provent Therapy, you can rest assured that your partner is taking care of their obstructive sleep apnea, as well as helping you both get a peaceful night&rsquo;s sleep.</p><h3>	Do Something.</h3><p>	Help yourself and your sleep partner by encouraging them to try Provent Therapy today. You can be an important part of your partner&rsquo;s success by:</p><ul>	<li>		Sharing the information on this website with your sleep partner</li>	<li>		Encouraging your sleep partner to talk to their doctor about Provent Therapy</li>	<li>		Asking your partner to register for our 10-night trial</li>	<li>		Encouraging your partner to stick with Provent Therapy, even if it takes several days to get used to it</li>	<li>		Reading the instructions together so you have the same expectations</li></ul><h3>	Watch and learn how Provent Therapy works</h3><p>	<video height=\"280\" id=\"vid\" poster=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/video/how_it_works.jpg\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/video/how_it_works.m4v\" tabindex=\"0\" width=\"372\"></video></p><p>	Obstructive sleep apnea (OSA) is characterized by repeated obstruction of the airway during sleep, which can lead to sleep disruption. Left untreated, OSA is associated to many health problems, including daytime sleepiness, heart attack, and high blood pressure.</p><p>	Traditionally, OSA is most often treated with a CPAP machine, which uses forced air to create pressure that keeps the airway open. This allows the patient to breathe more normally and avoid sleep disruption.</p><p>	Provent Therapy also uses pressure to keep the airway open. But instead of a machine, it uses the user&rsquo;s natural breathing to create pressure to keep the airway open. Like CPAP, Provent Therapy needs to be worn every night.</p><p>	Users apply the Provent Device over both nostrils right before they fall asleep. The device allows the patient to inhale freely. During exhalation, the air is directed through two small channels, which creates resistance and pressure that keeps the airway open. While awake, they should breathe through their mouth while breathing out; they will naturally switch to nasal breathing once asleep.</p><p>	In addition to better sleep, Provent Therapy has proven to improve daytime alertness, energy, and concentration, as well as reduce snoring in 83% of patients. Provent Therapy is an effective treatment for obstructive sleep apnea, allowing couples to sleep together more peacefully, and live their lives without compromise.</p><h3>	You can help your sleep partner succeed.</h3><p>	We&rsquo;ve found that having a supportive sleep partner increases the chance for patient success. Please encourage your partner to <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/10_night_trial\">sign up for our 10-night trial</a> of Provent Therapy today.</p><p>	It may take some time for them to get used to wearing the Provent Device. If you notice your partner needs help or is having difficulty adjusting, remind them of the benefits of treating their OSA and encourage them to stick with it. Or call us at <strong>1-888-SLP-WELL</strong> (1-888-757-9355) for personal advice and coaching.</p><p style=\"text-align: center\">	<strong><a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/how_to_use\">Get more details on how to use this CPAP alternative.</a></strong></p><p>	&nbsp;</p><hr /><address>	<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>1</sup><em> Data on file</em></span></address><address>	<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>2</sup> <em><span>Colrain</span> <span>IM</span>, Brooks S, Black <span>J</span>. A pilot evaluation of a nasal expiratory resistance device for the treatment of obstructive sleep apnea. Journal of Clinical Sleep <span>Medicine2008</span>;4(5):426-433</em></span></address>',0,0,'sleep_partners.template.php'),
(19,1,'page','published','2010-10-16 19:49:18','2011-03-01 05:12:46',6,'current_patients','Current Patients','<h1>	Current Provent Users</h1><p>	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><p>	Information and advice for people using Provent Therapy</p><h3>	Tips for Success</h3><p>	Provent Therapy often requires a period of adjustment. Some people get used to it right away; others may take up to a week or more to get used to it. <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/tips_for_success\">Here are some tips that Provent Therapy users have found useful</a>.</p><h3>	What to Expect</h3><p>	Though Provent Therapy seems simple, there are a few things to know in order to use it properly. To effectively relieve symptoms of OSA, the Provent Device needs to be worn every night, and certain steps need to be followed, which we&rsquo;ve outlined in the <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/what_to_expect\">&quot;What to Expect&quot; section of this Web site</a>.</p><h3>	Current Provent Users</h3><p>	<strong>Apply the Provent Device right before you fall asleep</strong>. Once applied, breathe out normally through your mouth (not through the device) when awake. You will naturally switch to nasal breathing once you&rsquo;re asleep.</p><p>	<strong>You should notice resistance when you exhale through your nose</strong>. This is normal, and means the device is working. But remember that while you are awake and trying to fall asleep, you should breathe out through your mouth. This will feel a lot more comfortable than breathing through the device.</p><p>	<strong>OSA is a chronic condition that requires treatment every night, so remember to make Provent Therapy a part of your bedtime routine</strong>. Provent Therapy is intended for single use only, so use a fresh set every night. You should store them in a cool, dry place (like near your bedside table).</p><p>	<strong>Some people adjust to Provent Therapy right away; others need more time</strong>. Have more questions?<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/faq\"> Get answers to common questions here</a>.&nbsp;If you need guidance or personal coaching, our trained experts can be reached at 1-888-SLP-WELL (1-888-757-9355). Remember, a little help may be all you need to get used to wearing PROVENT Therapy.</p><p>	Have you had success using Provent Therapy? If so, we would love to hear about it. Write to us and tell us your story and you may be the next patient featured on this site.</p><p>	If you&rsquo;d like to participate in research activities, or have questions, comments, or feedback, please email us at <a href=\"mailto:questions@ventusmedical.com?subject=Provent%20Therapy%20inquiry\">questions@ventusmedical.com</a>.</p>',0,0,'current_patient.template.php'),
(20,1,'page','published','2010-10-16 21:47:05','2011-03-01 05:14:50',100,'for_healthcare_professionals','For Healthcare Professionals','<h1>	A breakthrough treatment for obstructive sleep apnea</h1><p>	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><h3>	<span>AHI</span> improvement across multiple studies</h3><p>	In five studies<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>1-5</sup></span>, including the 19 center sham controlled study with 3 month follow-up and one studying <span>non-CPAP</span> compliant patients<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>4</sup></span>, <span>Provent</span> was shown to improve <span>AHI</span> consistently.</p><p>	<a href=\"/images/ConsistentAHIImprovement.gif\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"AHI Improvement\" src=\"..//images/uploads/consistentahiimprovement.png\" style=\"border-right-width: 0px; width: 460px; border-top-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; height: 254px; border-left-width: 0px\" /></a><br />	<a href=\"/images/ConsistentAHIImprovement.gif\" target=\"_blank\">Click for larger image</a></p><h3>	Snoring significantly reduced in <span>OSA</span> patients</h3><p>	In the first two published studies, <span>Provent</span> was shown to significantly reduce snoring (compared to baseline).&nbsp; In addition:</p><ul>	<li>		Clinical studies have shown that 83% of patients experienced a snoring reduction with <span>Provent</span> Therapy<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>1</sup></span></li>	<li>		<p>			Among <span>OSA</span> patients that snore, <span>Provent</span> Therapy reduced snoring to trace or none in 58% of patients<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><sup>6</sup></span></p>	</li></ul><p>	In completed clinical studies, no serious adverse events were reported.&nbsp; For a full list of potential adverse events, including contraindications, warnings and precautions, <a href=\"..//images/uploads/lbl0181-01_b_artwork,_provent_patient_&amp;_physician_ifu_%28p50_&amp;_p80%29.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">download the Instructions for Use</a>.</p><h3>	Learn more about Provent Therapy</h3><p>	<span>Provent</span> Therapy is an easy-to-use, discreet nasal device proven to significantly reduce <span>AHI</span> (Apnea <span>Hypopnea</span> Index), <span>ODI</span> (Oxygen <span>Desaturation</span> Index), and <span>OSA-related</span> snoring. Its breakthrough <span>MicroValve</span> design creates Expiratory Positive Airway Pressure (<span>EPAP</span>) that keeps the airway open, for better quality sleep and better daytime function. <span>Provent</span> Therapy is FDA-cleared for the treatment of <span>OSA.</span></p><ol style=\"margin-left: 40px\">	<li>		<a href=\"/clinical_information\">Review clinical data, publications, posters, and case reports about PROVENT Therapy.</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"/the_provent_patient\">Learn which OSA patients are best suited for Provent Therapy.</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"/full_prescribing_information\">Find everything you need in order to start prescribing PROVENT Therapy.</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"/success_stories\">Read about OSA patients who have embraced this new treatment.</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"/prescribe_now\">Fill out this form to get instructions, doctor order forms, and patient information.</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"/events\">Learn more about events and other opportunities to meet and chat with the makers of PROVENT Therapy.</a></li></ol><p>	Currently, Provent Therapy is only available in the United States, and is available through <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/supplier_locator\">these suppliers</a>.</p><p style=\"text-align: center\">	<strong><a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0217-01_a_generic_do_form.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Get started prescribing Provent Therapy now.&nbsp;Download a physician order form.</a></strong><span _fck_bookmark=\"1\" style=\"display: none\">&nbsp;</span></p><p>	If you have immediate questions, or would like to be contacted by a Provent representative, please email <a href=\"mailto:questions@ventusmedical.com?subject=Provent%20Therapy%20Inquiry&amp;body=%3CPlease%20enter%20your%20question%20here%3E\">questions@ventusmedical.com</a>.&nbsp;</p><hr /><address>	<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><small><sup>1</sup>Colrain&nbsp;IM, Brooks S, Black&nbsp;J. A pilot evaluation of a nasal expiratory resistance device for the treatment of obstructive sleep apnea. Journal of Clinical Sleep Medicine 2008;4(5):426-433.</small></span></address><address>	<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><small><sup>2</sup>Rosenthal&nbsp;L,&nbsp;Massie&nbsp;CA, et al. A&nbsp;Multicenter, Prospective Study of a Novel nasal&nbsp;EPAP&nbsp;Device in the Treatment of Obstructive Sleep Apnea: Efficacy and 30-Day Adherence. Journal of Clinical Sleep Medicine. 2009;5(6):532-537.</small></span></address><address>	<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><small><sup>3</sup>Berry&nbsp;RB,&nbsp;Massie&nbsp;C,&nbsp;Kryger&nbsp;MH. A Randomized Controlled Trial of Nasal Expiratory Resistance as a Treatment for Obstructive Sleep Apnea. Journal of Sleep and Sleep Disorders Research. 2010;33:A121.</small></span></address><address>	<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><small><sup>4</sup>Walsh&nbsp;JK, Griffin KS,&nbsp;Forst&nbsp;E, et al. A Convenient Expiratory Positive Airway Pressure Device is Effective for the Treatment of Sleep Apnea in Many Patients Non-adherent with Positive Airway Pressure. Journal of Sleep and Sleep Disorders Research. 2010;33:161-162.</small></span></address><address>	<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><small><sup>5</sup>Colrain&nbsp;I,&nbsp;Turlington&nbsp;S. The Use of a Nasal Resistance Valve to Treat Sleep Disordered Breathing. Journal of Sleep and Sleep Disorders Research. 2008;31:A172.</small></span></address><address>	<span style=\"font-size: 10px\"><small><sup>6</sup>Data on file</small></span></address>',0,0,'hcp_home.template.php'),
(21,1,'page','published','2010-10-16 22:18:56','2011-04-27 06:56:42',100,'clinical_information','Clinical Information','<h1>	Clinical Information</h1><p>	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><p>	Provent Therapy is a clinically proven alternative to CPAP therapy to treat obstructive sleep apnea and related snoring. Read about the device&rsquo;s innovative MicroValve technology, and how it stabilizes the airway using Expiratory Positive Airway Pressure (EPAP), which eliminates the need for masks, tubes, and electricity.</p><p>	We have extensive information available for you. You can read more about the clinical research behind this new OSA treatment below. Highlights include:</p><ul>	<li>		Results of over 15,000 study nights</li>	<li>		Completed six clinical studies with three more in process</li>	<li>		Two peer-reviewed, published studies in <em>Journal of Clinical Sleep Medicine</em>.</li>	<li>		Three additional peer-reviewed manuscripts accepted for publication in <em>Journal of Clinical Sleep Medicine, SLEEP, and Sleep Medicine (pending print publication)</em></li>	<li>		Nine poster presentations presented at SLEEP conferences</li></ul><h3>	Publications</h3><ul>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/jcsmarticle01.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">A Pilot Evaluation of a Nasal Expiratory Resistance Device for the Treatment of Obstructive Sleep Apnea</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/jcsmarticle02.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">A Multicenter, Prospective Study of a Novel Nasal EPAP Device in the Treatment of Obstructive Sleep Apnea: Efficacy and 30-Day Adherence</a></li></ul><h3>	Posters</h3><ul>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/pdf03_colrain_poster_session.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">The Use of a Nasal Resistance Valve to Treat Sleep Disordered Breathing</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0096-01_poster_session.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Nasal EPAP &ndash; Efficacy and Physiologic Mechanism of Action</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0077-01_poster_session.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Modeling the Effectiveness of Treatments for Obstructive Sleep Apnea/Hypopnea</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0078-01_poster.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Success Rates of Nasal Expiratory Positive Airway Pressure (nEPAP) Via Expiratory Resistive Load for the Treatment of Obstructive Sleep Apnea</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0155-01_a_poster_2010.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">A Convenient Expiratory Positive Airway Pressure Device is Effective for the Treatment of Obstructive Sleep Apnea in Many Patients Non-Adherent with CPAP</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0154-01_a_artwork_poster_sleep_2010_cpap_rejecter_research_(poster_format).pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Dissatisfaction with OSA Management Among CPAP Rejecters and the Role of the Primary Care Physician</a></li></ul><h3>	Abstracts</h3><ul>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0163-01_a_abstract.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">A Convenient Expiratory Positive Airway Pressure Device Is Effective For The Treatment Of Sleep Apnea In Many Patients Non-Adherent With Positive Airway Pressure</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0158-01_a_artwork_berry_sleep_2010_abstract.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">A Randomized Controlled Trial of Nasal Expiratory Resistance as a Treatment for Obstructive Sleep Apnea</a></li></ul><h3>	Case Studies</h3><ul>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0069-01_a_artwork_provent_case_study_w_dr_stolz_and_patient.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Managing Obstructive Sleep Apnea with Provent&reg; Sleep Apnea Therapy</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0115-01_b_artwork_provent_therapy_case_study_with_dr_berland_and_patient_mt.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Treating Obstructive Sleep Apnea (OSA) Using Home Sleep Testing and Provent&reg; Sleep Apnea Therapy</a></li></ul><h3>	Articles</h3><ul>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/mdd.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Ventus gets &quot;bulletproof&quot; data that Provent works</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0207-01_a_sleep_apnea_devices_website.pdf\">Sleep Apnea Devices: The Changing of the Guard</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0257-01_a_wallstreetjournal.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><em>The Wall Street Journal</em>: Good Night&#39;s Sleep by a Nose</a></li></ul><h3>	View the Patient Discussion Guide and <a href=\"/images/uploads/lbl0227-01_a_one-page_acclimation_guide_for_dmes.pdf\">Some Helpful Tips</a></h3><p>	Clinical experience indicates OSA patients who know what to expect with Provent Therapy are more likely to adhere to treatment. <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0146-01_a_hcp_guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Here is a step-by-step guide to discussing it with your patients</a>.</p><h3>	Download a Doctor Order (Prescription) Form&nbsp;</h3><p>	Prescribe Provent Therapy, a new treatment for OSA, by downloading a <span _fck_bookmark=\"1\" style=\"display: none\">&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0217-01_a_generic_do_form.pdf\">doctor order form</a>&nbsp;.&nbsp;</p>',0,0,'hcp.template.php'),
(22,1,'page','published','2010-10-16 22:19:18','2011-03-01 05:17:47',101,'the_provent_patient','The Provent Patient','<h1>	The Provent Patient</h1><p>	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><h3>	See how OSA patients enjoy better sleep and brighter days with Provent Therapy.</h3><p>	For increasing numbers of patients, Provent Therapy has become a treatment of choice for obstructive sleep apnea. Some are CPAP rejectors who have achieved compliance with Provent Therapy. Others use CPAP at home, but find Provent to be an ideal adjunctive OSA treatment for traveling. In this section, you can read more about Provent patients and their stories.</p><p>	Provent Therapy is indicated for the treatment of OSA. Physicians have prescribed this device to the following patients</p><ul>	<li>		<p>			Those who have given up on CPAP Therapy</p>	</li>	<li>		<p>			Those who are using CPAP, but&nbsp; not all night, every night</p>	</li>	<li>		<p>			People who have been recently diagnosed with mild to moderate OSA</p>	</li>	<li>		<p>			People who need an adjunctive therapy for occasional travel</p>	</li></ul><h3>	Case Studies</h3><ul>	<li>		<a href=\"..//images/uploads/msm0069-01_a_artwork_provent_case_study_w_dr_stolz_and_patient.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Managing Obstructive Sleep Apnea with <span><span><span><span>Provent&reg;</span></span></span></span> Sleep Apnea Therapy</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"..//images/uploads/msm0115-01_b_artwork_provent_therapy_case_study_with_dr_berland_and_patient_mt.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Treating Obstructive Sleep Apnea (<span>OSA</span>) Using Home Sleep Testing and <span><span><span><span>Provent&reg;</span></span></span></span> Sleep Apnea Therapy</a></li></ul><h3>	Testimonials</h3><p>	<strong>Angela, Bayside, New York</strong><br />	A CPAP rejector and travel enthusiast, Angela discovered that, with Provent Therapy, she could experience measurable improvement in her OSA while retaining the freedom to travel without the hassle and maintenance of a machine.</p><p>	<strong>Mar&iacute;a, Middle Island, Long Island</strong><br />	For years, Maria had struggled with OSA treatments, including CPAP and oral appliances. With Provent Therapy, her apnea is treated, her snoring is reduced and she is able to resume her highly active lifestyle.</p><p style=\"text-align: center\">	<a href=\"/success_stories\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Read more about Provent Therapy success stories</strong></a>.</p><p>	Provent Therapy is contraindicated in certain patients. <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/lbl0181-01_proventpatientphysicianifu.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">See IFU for contraindications and warnings</a>.&nbsp;</p>',0,0,'hcp.template.php'),
(23,1,'page','published','2010-10-16 22:19:52','2011-03-01 05:18:53',102,'full_prescribing_information','Full Prescribing Information','<h1>	Full Prescribing Information</h1><p>	<br />	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><p>	Here is some helpful information to discuss Provent Therapy with your patients to help set appropriate expectations and ensure optimum success.</p><p>	Clinical experience indicates that OSA patients who understand what to expect with Provent Therapy are more likely to adhere to treatment. Here are some topics to discuss with your patients:</p><h4 style=\"margin-left: 40px\">	Introduce Provent Therapy</h4><ul style=\"margin-left: 40px\">	<li>		<a href=\"images/uploads/lbl0227-01_a_one-page_acclimation_guide_for_dmes.pdf\">A novel Expiratory Positive Airway Pressure device to treat OSA</a></li>	<li>		Consists of a small valve attached to a hypoallergenic adhesive placed over each nostril; valves create expiratory resistance while providing minimal resistance to inspiration</li>	<li>		Clinically proven, safe and easy to use, portable, quiet, and disposable</li></ul><h4 style=\"margin-left: 40px\">	Help apply the device</h4><ul style=\"margin-left: 40px\">	<li>		<a href=\"/how_to_use\">Apply Provent Therapy over each nostril</a></li>	<li>		Explain the feeling of resistance upon exhalation</li></ul><h4 style=\"margin-left: 40px\">	Educate your patient and set expectations</h4><ul style=\"margin-left: 40px\">	<li>		Pressure means it&rsquo;s working: The patient will feel pressure; explain this is normal and means that Provent Therapy is working</li>	<li>		Breathe out through the mouth: The patient will shift to nasal breathing when asleep, but should breathe through the mouth when awake</li>	<li>		Don&rsquo;t feel anxious: The patient may experience anxiety when first wearing Provent Therapy; this is normal and should improve with repeat usage</li>	<li>		Keep water at bedside: Some patients may experience dry mouth while wearing the device; advise the patient to keep a glass of water nearby</li>	<li>		Give it a few days: If the patient has difficulty using Provent Therapy the first few nights, it&rsquo;s okay to remove the device and try again the next night; it should become more comfortable</li></ul><h4 style=\"margin-left: 40px\">	Evaluate your patient&rsquo;s results</h4><ul style=\"margin-left: 40px\">	<li>		Follow up with patient to assess efficacy with <a href=\"/images/uploads/nasal_cannula_data_sheet_msm0016-01_b_11-8.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">the PROVENT Nasal Cannula</a></li>	<li>		Additional testing on PROVENT Therapy may be recommended</li></ul><h3>	Prescribe Provent Therapy</h3><p>	There are 3 easy ways to prescribe Provent Sleep Apnea Therapy for your patient:</p><ol style=\"margin-left: 40px\">	<li>		Complete and Fax a (Prescription) <span _fck_bookmark=\"1\" style=\"display: none\">&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0217-01_a_generic_do_form.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Doctor Order Form</a> and fax or mail it to the distributor of your choice by following the instructions on the form.</li>	<li>		Contact a supplier. <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/supplier_locator\">Click here to choose from a list of suppliers</a>.</li>	<li>		Have a Sales Representative contact you. <a href=\"mailto:questions@ventusmedical?subject=Sales%20Representative%20Contact&amp;body=%3CPlease%20enter%20contact%20information%20here%3E\">Click here to request contact</a>.</li></ol><p>	Please note that you can order a 10-night Trial Pack and/or a 30-night supply for your patient. Once the supplier receives your DO (prescription) form, the patient will be contacted within 3 days to confirm shipment and collect payment.</p>',0,0,'hcp.template.php'),
(25,1,'page','published','2010-10-16 22:20:32','2011-03-02 04:01:23',104,'prescribe_now','Prescribe Now','<p>	Here is how you can prescribe Provent Sleep Apnea Therapy for your patient:</p><ol>	<li>		Download and complete the attached <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/uploads/msm0209-01_genericdoform_web.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Doctor Order Form </a>on behalf of your patient.</li>	<li>		Choose a supplier. <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/supplier_locator\">Click here to choose from a list of suppliers</a>.</li>	<li>		Fax the completed Doctor Order form to the supplier of your choice.&nbsp;</li></ol><p>	Please note that you can order a 10-night Trial Pack and/or a 30-night supply for your patient. Once the supplier receives your DO (prescription) form, the patient will be contacted within 3 days to confirm shipment and collect payment.</p><p>	To obtain updates and more detailed&nbsp;information about prescribing Provent Sleep Apnea Therapy, please complete and submit the form below.</p><p>	Provent Therapy is currently available in the US.</p>',0,0,'prescribe.template.php'),
(26,1,'page','published','2010-10-16 22:20:41','2011-05-19 02:47:36',105,'events','Events','<h1>	Provent Therapy may be coming to a town near you<br />	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></h1><p>	See below for our schedule of events, where you can meet with representatives from Ventus Medical and learn more about this breakthrough device for treating obstructive sleep apnea.</p><h3>	Upcoming Events</h3><ul>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.thoracic.org/conference/index.php\" target=\"_blank\">ATS 2011, May 13 - 18</a></li>	<li>		<a href=\"http://www.sleepmeeting.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Sleep 2011, June 11 - 15</a></li></ul><h3>	<br />	In The News</h3><p>	Welcome to our news page. Check here for frequent updates on press coverage and media appearances featuring Ventus Medical and Provent Therapy. We invite you to read these articles about Provent Therapy:</p><ul>	<li>		<p>			<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/biz0051-01.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span dir=\"ltr\" title=\"\">PRESENTATION AT AMERICAN THORACIC SOCIETY<br />			ANNUAL MEETING FURTHER DEMONSTRATES MECHANISM<br />			OF ACTION FOR PROVENT&reg; SLEEP APNEA THERAPY </span></a></p>	</li>	<li>		<p>			<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HmfufUmxBbc\" target=\"_blank\"><span dir=\"ltr\" title=\"Provent: New Therapy for Sleep Apnea\">Provent: New Therapy for Sleep Apnea</span></a></p>		<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HmfufUmxBbc\" target=\"_blank\"> </a></li>	<li>		<p>			<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HmfufUmxBbc\" target=\"_blank\"> </a><a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/uploads/mdd.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Ventus</span> gets &quot;bulletproof&quot; data that <span>Provent</span> works</a></p>	</li>	<li>		<p>			<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0207-01_a_sleep_apnea_devices_website.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Sleep Apnea Devices: The Changing Of The Guard</a></p>	</li>	<li>		<p>			<a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/msm0257-01_a_wallstreetjournal.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><em>The Wall Street Journal</em>: Good Night&#39;s Sleep by a Nose</a></p>	</li></ul>',0,0,'hcp.template.php'),
(28,1,'page','published','2010-11-13 06:26:32','2011-03-01 05:20:54',1,'tips_for_success','Tips For Success','<h1>	Learn how to get the most out of Provent Therapy</h1><p>	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><p>	Welcome to Provent Sleep Apnea Therapy. Treating your sleep apnea can help you achieve a healthier and more productive day. And with Provent Therapy, you should experience less apnea-related snoring. If this is your first time trying Provent, you may get used to the device immediately. Fantastic! If you don&rsquo;t, stick with it. Wearing Provent Therapy may take some time to get used to.</p><h3>	Important steps before starting:</h3><ol>	<li>		The device works by making it harder to breathe out. This creates pressure, which keeps your airway open</li>	<li>		Breathe out through your mouth (not though the device) when awake. You&rsquo;ll naturally breathe through the device when you fall asleep</li>	<li>		It may take time to get used to wearing the device. Give it a few days; it should feel a lot better</li>	<li>		Take it off. If you wake up during the night and feel uncomfortable, just take it off. Try again tomorrow; it should get better</li></ol><p>	<strong>Need help?</strong> We want you to be successful, so if you have any questions, or need help, call us at 1-888-SLP-WELL (1-888-757-9355)</p><p>	Please refer to the <a href=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com//images/uploads/lbl0181-01_proventpatientphysicianifu.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Provent Instructions</a> for additional information.</p>',19,0,'tips.template.php'),
(29,1,'page','published','2010-11-13 06:40:27','2011-03-01 05:22:11',2,'what_to_expect','What To Expect','<h1>	What To Expect</h1><h3>	Here are some suggestions for using (and getting used to) Provent Therapy.</h3><p>	<span class=\"st_sharethis\" displaytext=\"ShareThis\"><img border=\"0\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/space.gif\" width=\"1\" /></span></p><p>	If you&rsquo;ve been prescribed Provent Therapy, you may be surprised to see how different it is from other OSA treatments (such as CPAP machines) you might have tried. The Provent Device uses pressure to keep the airway open during sleep, but instead of forced air, it&rsquo;s powered by your own breathing.</p><p>	Each Provent Device features a breakthrough MicroValve design that creates resistance when you exhale. This Expiratory Positive Airway Pressure (EPAP) helps treat your apnea, reducing snoring and helping you get a more refreshing night&rsquo;s sleep.</p><p>	The device attaches over each nostril with a hypoallergenic adhesive, and is designed for single use. So use a fresh set every night. Apply it right before you go to sleep, and follow these steps:</p><p>	<strong>STEP 1 &ndash; Inhale</strong></p><p>	Inhale through your mouth or through the device, whichever is more comfortable for you to fall asleep.</p><p>	<strong>STEP 2 &ndash; Exhale</strong></p><p>	Breathe out through your mouth.&nbsp; If you try breathing through your nose, notice the significant resistance. This is normal, and tells you the device is working.&nbsp; And remember, it&rsquo;s recommended to just breathe out through your mouth while awake.&nbsp; You will naturally switch to nasal breathing once you&rsquo;re asleep, effectively &ldquo;turning on&rdquo; the device.</p><p>	<strong>STEP 3 &ndash; Relax</strong></p><p>	Do not engage in any activity while wearing the device&mdash;just try to fall asleep once you&rsquo;ve applied it.</p><p>	Keep a glass of water near your bedside, in case you wake up with a dry mouth.</p><p>	<strong>STEP 4 &ndash; REPEAT</strong></p><p>	The Provent Device should be worn every night.&nbsp; If you have trouble using the device, keep trying. Many users just need time to get used to it.&nbsp; This is normal.</p><p>	<strong>STEP 5 &ndash; COMMIT</strong></p><p>	Use all the devices provided in the pack. Eventually, Provent Therapy should become part of your nightly routine.</p><p>	Need more help using Provent? <a href=\"http://96.31.169.199//images/uploads/lbl0173-01_a_artwork,_provent_application_and_acclimation_guide.pdf\">Download this Application and Usage Guide</a>.</p>',19,0,'home.template.php'),
(35,1,'page','published','2011-01-24 07:51:19','2011-03-01 05:22:41',0,'reduce_snoring_and_treat_your_obstructive_sleep_apnea','Reduce Snoring And Treat Your Obstructive Sleep Apnea','<p>	<img alt=\"Provent Therapy couple\" src=\"http://www.proventtherapy.com/images/land_snore.png\" style=\"width: 460px; height: 305px\" /></p><p>	Snoring is a troubling symptom of obstructive sleep apnea and can disrupt your sleep and your relationship with your partner. Provent Therapy works by keeping your airway open, reducing vibration in the restricted airway that causes the snoring. This can mean better sleep for you and a more peaceful sleep experience for your partner.</p>',0,0,'snoring_one.template.php'),
